<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="131" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="131">
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Campello, Vaz, Mermudes &amp; Silveira" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Memoan" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Memoan conani" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conani">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Memoan conani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a masculine noun in the genitive case. The species is named in honor of Mauricio Conan Mendes Correa de Oliveira. Conan was a biology student at the Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, deceased since January 2019, and was a dear friend of the first author.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="131" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="131">
Labial palp with two palpomeres (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Memoan conani sp. nov., head A dorsal B ventral C frontal D lateral E posterior F occipital; antenna G dorsal H lateral. Scale bar: 0.5 mm (A-H). Note the gular margins contiguous (arrow)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1114.77692.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720411" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">3B, F</figureCitation>
); scape as long as pedicel (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Memoan conani sp. nov., head A dorsal B ventral C frontal D lateral E posterior F occipital; antenna G dorsal H lateral. Scale bar: 0.5 mm (A-H). Note the gular margins contiguous (arrow)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1114.77692.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720411" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">3G, H</figureCitation>
); apical antennomere entire, lacking a subdivision or vestigial joint (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Memoan conani sp. nov., head A dorsal B ventral C frontal D lateral E posterior F occipital; antenna G dorsal H lateral. Scale bar: 0.5 mm (A-H). Note the gular margins contiguous (arrow)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1114.77692.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720411" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">3G, H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
